Legend (levels from left to right):
Root - Utility keyword meaning that this is so-called 'Utility tree' - analysis of quality attributes (QA) impact on business value and architecture.
The second level - major QAs this system must support to be viable.
The third level - the refinement of QAs.
The fourth level (Magic Mint color) - architecture significant requirements (ASR) to meet corresponding QA.
Yellow labels - the first letter is the business value of ASR -
H - Must have
M - Important, but if omitted, that not lead to project failure
L - Nice to have
the second letter is architecture impact of ASR -
H - Significant effect
M - Somewhat affects
L - Little effect
